ront of Barracks will be congested with all of the cadets trying to depart at the same time  Vehicles should remain parked on the Parade Ground  when possible  and the cadet s belongings carried to the vehicle  The VMI Police needs your assistance and patience to ensure that the cadet departure is accomplished in the quickest and safest manner possible  Inclement Weather Parking If inclement weather makes parking on the Parade Ground impractical  additional parking may be found throughout post in designated parking areas  Parking in Walking Distance Other City Parking   On weekends  there are no time limits for parking on the street or in city parking lots  Contact the Lexington Visitor Center for more information  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 